<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 22 at 5:28PM CDT until July 22 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 600 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN BULLOCK AND SOUTH CENTRAL MACON COUNTIES...
At 528 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hardaway, or 11
miles northwest of Union Springs, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Hardaway, Franklin Field, Sedgefield, Mitchell and Fort Davis.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
